Summary: Green light fell from the sky and seemed to shoot forward and fade away
divs: Sighting DetailsI was in the backyard late this evening with my husband and our 2 dogs when I noticed this green "star". As soon as I looked at it, it just dropped out of the sky and seemed to shoot itself forward into the sky (south from where I was looking). Then it just faded away. My husband caught the tail end of what I saw. I've also seen a purple "star" do the same thing except move west to east in the sky. Both with in a matter of 10 seconds or less.
